io.servicetalk.grpc.api

Class GrpcMessageEncodings

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.servicetalk.grpc.api.GrpcMessageEncodings

  • public final class GrpcMessageEncodings
extends java.lang.Object
    Default available encoding implementations. Encoding none() is always supported regardless of the client or server settings. all() is a set that includes all default encodings deflate() and gzip().

      • encodingFor

        @Nullable
public static GrpcMessageEncoding encodingFor(java.util.Collection<GrpcMessageEncoding> allowedList,
                                                        @Nullable
                                                        java.lang.String name)
        Returns a GrpcMessageEncoding that matches the name. Returns null if name is null or empty. If name is 'identity' this will always result in NONE regardless of its presence in the allowedList.
        Parameters:
        allowedList - the source list to find a matching encoding in
        name - the encoding name used for the matching predicate
        Returns:
        an encoding from the allowed-list matching the name, otherwise null if name is null or empty
